Feature: Files Error Scenarios

  Background:
    Given I am authenticated

  Scenario: Upload file without authentication

    Given I am not authenticated
    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | 019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846 |
      | files | test-document.pdf                     |

    Then the response status code should be 401

  Scenario: Upload file with invalid item ID format

    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | invalid-id        |
      | files | test-document.pdf |

    Then the response status code should be 400

  Scenario: Upload file without files parameter

    When I POST the payload to "/api/v1/file/upload" with body:
    """
    {
      "id": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846"
    }
    """
    Then the response status code should be 400

  Scenario: Upload file without id parameter

    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | files | test-document.pdf |

    Then the response status code should be 400

  Scenario: List files with invalid item ID format

    When I GET "/api/v1/file/invalid-id"
    Then the response status code should be 400

  Scenario: Download file with invalid file ID format

    When I GET "/api/v1/file/download/invalid-id"
    Then the response status code should be 400

  Scenario: Delete file with invalid file ID format

    When I DELETE "/api/v1/file/delete/invalid-id"
    Then the response status code should be 400

  Scenario: Delete files by item with invalid item ID format

    When I DELETE "/api/v1/file/delete/item/invalid-id"
    Then the response status code should be 400

  Scenario: Upload file exceeding maximum size limit

    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | 019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846 |
      | files | huge-file.zip                         |
      | size  | 1073741824                            |

    Then the response status code should be 413
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    {
      "message": "File size exceeds maximum allowed size"
    }
    """

  Scenario: Upload file with unsupported file type

    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | 019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846 |
      | files | malicious.exe                         |

    Then the response status code should be 415
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    {
      "message": "Unsupported file type"
    }
    """

  Scenario: Download file when S3 is unavailable

    Given the following file exists in the database:
    """
    {
      "id": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850",
      "itemId": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846",
      "fileName": "document.pdf",
      "urlS3": "https://bucket.s3.amazonaws.com/items/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_document.pdf",
      "size": 1024,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-31T10:00:00Z"
    }
    """

    Given S3 service is unavailable

    When I GET "/api/v1/file/download/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850"
    Then the response status code should be 503
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    {
      "message": "Storage service temporarily unavailable"
    }
    """

  Scenario: Upload file when S3 is unavailable

    Given S3 service is unavailable

    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | 019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846 |
      | files | test-document.pdf                     |

    Then the response status code should be 503
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    {
      "message": "Storage service temporarily unavailable"
    }
    """

  Scenario: Delete file when S3 is unavailable

    Given the following file exists in the database:
    """
    {
      "id": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850",
      "itemId": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846",
      "fileName": "document.pdf",
      "urlS3": "https://bucket.s3.amazonaws.com/items/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_document.pdf",
      "size": 1024,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-31T10:00:00Z"
    }
    """

    Given S3 service is unavailable

    When I DELETE "/api/v1/file/delete/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850"
    Then the response status code should be 503
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    {
      "message": "Storage service temporarily unavailable"
    }
    """

